This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it introduces a method for secure inference with deep neural networks on untrusted devices. It also mentions verifying the integrity of the inference computation to ensure it has not been manipulated by an attacker, which is a key aspect of cryptography and security. 

It is also likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it deals with deep neural networks and their inference. 

The cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the configuration of CheckNet to provide different levels of security depending on compute/communication budgets, which is related to system design and control. 

The cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category is another possibility as the paper deals with deep neural networks, which are a key component of AI. 

Finally, the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses a method for ensuring the integrity of software computations, which is related to software engineering.
